# ============================================================================
# {{DOMAIN_NAME}} Wiki — Environment + Intake Template
# ============================================================================
#
# Copy this file to `.env` and fill in whatever you have. Anything you don't
# have yet, leave blank — gather it across the first few sessions.
#
#   cp .env.example .env
#   # then open .env and edit
#
# `.env` is gitignored — it never leaves your laptop. Only `.env.example`
# is committed. Never commit a filled-in `.env`.
#
# Two kinds of values live here:
#
#   (A) API KEYS — actual environment variables consumed by MCP servers and
#       lint scripts. These NEED to be in `.env` for the tools to work.
#
#   (B) DOMAIN INTAKE DATA — a checklist of facts the wiki needs (entity
#       names, URLs, identifiers, goals). The canonical home for this data
#       is the relevant wiki page — but listing it here too gives you ONE
#       document you can scan when prepping for a session.
#
# Convention: lines that start `#` are comments. Lines like `KEY=` are
# fields to fill. Lines like `# KEY=` are optional / future fields.
#
# ============================================================================
# (A) API KEYS — required for MCP servers + scripts
# ============================================================================

# Brave Search API — for the brave-search MCP server.
# Used for: web search, news, local-business lookups, fact-checking.
# Get a key at https://api.search.brave.com/  (free tier: 2,000 queries/mo).
BRAVE_API_KEY=

# Exa API — for the exa MCP server.
# Used for: higher-signal web search, deep research, GitHub repo crawling
#           for Phase-0 tool audits.
# Get a key at https://exa.ai/  (paid; pay-per-search).
EXA_API_KEY=

# Add additional API keys here as the workflow expands (Google APIs,
# DataForSEO, OpenAI, vendor-specific services, etc.).

# ============================================================================
# (B) DOMAIN INTAKE DATA — customize per workspace
# ============================================================================
#
# Replace this entire section with intake fields specific to your domain.
# Examples from sister wikis:
#
#   • Business profile (B&M wiki): legal name, GBP URLs, addresses, social
#     handles, booking platform, POS, CRM
#   • Creator profile (creator-marketing wiki): platform handles, follower
#     counts, content niche, goals, hard constraints
#   • Trading profile (finance wiki): broker, account size, risk tolerance,
#     watchlist tickers, prediction-market accounts
#   • Print farm profile (3d-printing wiki): printers, materials, slicers,
#     store URL
#
# Group fields under section headers `B.N — <topic>` and add a comment line
# pointing at the wiki page where each value gets promoted:
#
#   # Promote into: wiki/entities/companies/<slug>.md (Raw Concept + Narrative)
#
# If you don't know what intake fields you need yet, leave this section as a
# single TODO and fill it in once the first ingest pass has clarified the
# domain's natural shape.
#
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# B.1 — (placeholder; replace per workspace)
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------

# TODO: define domain-specific intake fields here.

# ============================================================================
# End of intake template.
#
# When this file is fully filled in:
#   1. Copy the API keys into your real `.env`
#   2. Promote the intake data into the relevant wiki pages
#   3. Run `python3 scripts/wiki_lint.py` to confirm the wiki is healthy
#   4. Start the first ingest cycle — see CLAUDE.md "Ingest" operation
# ============================================================================
